{"parse":{"title":"Bath Festival of Children's Literature","pageid":12262654,"revid":834363443,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">\"BKLF\" redirects here. For the transcription factor, see <a href=\"/wiki/KLF3\" title=\"KLF3\">KLF3</a>.</div>\n<p><b>The Bath Children's Literature Festival</b> (also known as Bath Kids' Lit Fest) is an annual book festival held in <a href=\"/wiki/Bath,_Somerset\" title=\"Bath, Somerset\">Bath, Somerset</a> aimed at children's books. The festival features a variety of authors, poets, illustrators and storytellers. It typically lasts ten days, spanning two weekends. Various events are organised in the city during this time,<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> as well as events at local schools in the central week.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Festival has been organised by John and Gill McLay since its creation in 2008.\n</p><p>The Festival has attracted a wealth of popular and talented guests, including the <a href=\"/wiki/Children%27s_Laureate\" title=\"Children&#39;s Laureate\">Children's Laureate</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Rosen\" title=\"Michael Rosen\">Michael Rosen</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Michael_Morpurgo\" title=\"Michael Morpurgo\">Michael Morpurgo</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Jacqueline_Wilson\" title=\"Jacqueline Wilson\">Jacqueline Wilson</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Harry_Hill\" title=\"Harry Hill\">Harry Hill</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Meg_Cabot\" title=\"Meg Cabot\">Meg Cabot</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Axel_Scheffler\" title=\"Axel Scheffler\">Axel Scheffler</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Bath_Festival_of_Children%27s_Literature&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a